I"x<p><em>Long Distance Relationships</em> was a public art piece installed in phone booth on Franklin St, Melbourne. The user was invited to call a hotline and were provided with a series of choices.</p>

<p>Synthetic natural
compositions and different sonic textures were played to represent different situations. The intent was to take people out of the busy surrounds of the CBD and augment their experience. Below is a recording testing the user interface.</p>

